    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite </p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your<strong> pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded spring greens</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the veg is starting to soften, drain, then add your <strong>jumbo king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for a further 4 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> red chilli relish</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> rice vinegar</strong> and <strong>soy sauce </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your<strong> stir-fry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything's fragrant, add the <strong>stir-fry sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further, giving it a good mix up until everything is coated in the sauce and the prawns are cooked through \u2013 these are your<strong> ginger & chilli jumbo king prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-and-chilli-jumbo-king-prawns-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>ginger & chilli jumbo king prawns </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
